{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.5 [SDTM Core Designations]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "An Expected variable is any variable necessary to make a record useful in the context of a specific domain. Expected variables may contain some null values, but in most cases will not contain null values for every record. When the study does not include the data item for an expected variable, however, a null column must still be included in the dataset, and a comment must be included in the Define-XML document to state that the study does not include the data item.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Core column indicates how a variable is classified (see Section 4.1.5, SDTM Core Designations).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.1.5"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If it is necessary to represent relationships between data that are hierarchical in nature (e.g., a parent record must be observed before child records), then establish a domain pair (e.g., MB/MS, PC/PP). Note: Domain pairs have been modeled for microbiology data (MB/MS domains) and pharmacokinetics (PK) data (PC/PP domains) to enable dataset-level relationships to be described using RELREC. The domain pair uses DOMAIN as an identifier to group parent records (e.g., MB) from child records (e.g., MS) and enables a dataset-level relationship to be described in RELREC. Without using DOMAIN to facilitate description of the data relationships, RELREC, as currently defined, could not be used without introducing a variable that would group data like DOMAIN.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
